div.p: Organisational topics of a Expert Group are realised in their own way of working.
New standards or changes of a standard are implemented on an on branch in the Standards repo.

p.span: e.g. Kits, Reference Implementation, API Specification, Protocols, Sample Data, Architecture, Documentation, Deployment Scripts, Tutorials etc..

span.font: e.g. Standards (cause of adaptations in Semantic Models, Logic/Schema, API Specification, Protocols), Whitepaper (which might end up in a Kits adaptation) etc.

p.span: SetUp ExpertGroup, Promotion of UseCases etc..
All intended changes in Tractus-X must be submitted as feature proposal in the SIG release repo. Feature proposals must then be refined and broken into development tasks.

div.p: Change requests of Standard must be submitted via CX Houston.
All organisational topics an Expert Groups wants to work own might be broken down in tasks in their private work space.

p.span: Development tasks need to be created in the repository of the affected component.
